.TH "egress_pkey_check" 9 "egress_pkey_check" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
egress_pkey_check \- check P_KEY of a packet
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" egress_pkey_check
.BI "(struct hfi1_pportdata *ppd "  ","
.BI "u32 slid "  ","
.BI "u16 pkey "  ","
.BI "u8 sc5 "  ","
.BI "int8_t s_pkey_index "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "ppd" 12
Physical IB port data
.IP "slid" 12
SLID for packet
.IP "pkey" 12
PKEY for header
.IP "sc5" 12
SC for packet
.IP "s_pkey_index" 12
It will be used for look up optimization for kernel contexts
only. If it is negative value, then it means user contexts is calling this
function.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
It checks if hdr's pkey is valid.
.SH "RETURN"
0 on success, otherwise, 1
